9162afaf2f60a172453","type":"image"},{"sequence":2,"text":"Input: s1 = \"aabcc\", s2 = \"dbbca\", s3 = \"aadbbcbcac\"\nOutput: true\nExplanation: One way to obtain s3 is:\nSplit s1 into s1 = \"aa\" + \"bc\" + \"c\", and s2 into s2 = \"dbbc\" + \"a\".\nInterleaving the two splits, we get \"aa\" + \"dbbc\" + \"bc\" + \"a\" + \"c\" = \"aadbbcbcac\".\nSince s3 can be obtained by interleaving s1 and s2, we return true.","type":"code"},{"sequence":3,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":4,"text":"Input: s1 = \"aabcc\", s2 = \"dbbca\", s3 = \"aadbbbaccc\"\nOutput: false\nExplanation: Notice how it is impossible to interleave s2 with any other string to obtain s3.","type":"code"},{"sequence":5,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":6,"text":"Input: s1 = \"\", s2 = \"\", s3 = \"\"\nOutput: true","type":"code"},{"sequence":7,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `0 <= s1.length, s2.length <= 100`\n\n- `0 <= s3.length <= 200`\n\n- `s1`, `s2`, and `s3` consist of lowercase English letters.\n\n**Follow up:** Could you solve it using only `O(s2.length)` additional memory space?","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["String","Dynamic Programming"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"Given strings `s1`, `s2`, and `s3`, find whether `s3` is formed by an **interleaving** of `s1` and `s2`.\n\nAn **interleaving** of two strings `s` and `t` is a configuration where `s` and `t` are divided into `n` and `m` [substrings](leetcode-keyword) respectively, such that:\n\n- `s = s1 + s2 + ... + sn`\n\n- `t = t1 + t2 + ... + tm`\n\n- `|n - m| <= 1`\n\n- The **interleaving** is `s1 + t1 + s2 + t2 + s3 + t3 + ...` or `t1 + s1 + t2 + s2 + t3 + s3 + ...`\n\n**Note:** `a + b` is the concatenation of strings `a` and `b`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n[[img:leetcode_seed/assets/problems/0097-interleaving-string/97-interleave.jpg]]\n\nInput: s1 = \"aabcc\", s2 = \"dbbca\", s3 = \"aadbbcbcac\"\nOutput: true\nExplanation: One way to obtain s3 is:\nSplit s1 into s1 = \"aa\" + \"bc\" + \"c\", and s2 into s2 = \"dbbc\" + \"a\".\nInterleaving the two splits, we get \"aa\" + \"dbbc\" + \"bc\" + \"a\" + \"c\" = \"aadbbcbcac\".\nSince s3 can be obtained by interleaving s1 and s2, we return true.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: s1 = \"aabcc\", s2 = \"dbbca\", s3 = \"aadbbbaccc\"\nOutput: false\nExplanation: Notice how it is impossible to interleave s2 with any other string to obtain s3.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: s1 = \"\", s2 = \"\", s3 = \"\"\nOutput: true\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `0 <= s1.length, s2.length <= 100`\n\n- `0 <= s3.length <= 200`\n\n- `s1`, `s2`, and `s3` consist of lowercase English letters.\n\n**Follow up:** Could you solve it using only `O(s2.length)` additional memory space?","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/interleaving-string/","problemName":"Interleaving String","problemNumber":97,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Given strings `s1`, `s2`, and `s3`, find whether `s3` is formed by an **interleaving** of `s1` and `s2`.\n\nAn **interleaving** of two strings `s` and `t` is a configuration where `s` and `t` are divided into `n` and `m` [substrings](leetcode-keyword) respectively, such that:\n\n- `s = s1 + s2 + ... + sn`\n\n- `t = t1 + t2 + ... + tm`\n\n- `|n - m| <= 1`\n\n- The **interleaving** is `s1 + t1 + s2 + t2 + s3 + t3 + ...` or `t1 + s1 + t2 + s2 + t3 + s3 + ...`\n\n**Note:** `a + b` is the concatenation of strings `a` and `b`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/jpeg","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/0097-interleaving-string/97-interleave.jpg","sequence":1,"sha256":"8f66f2e27a8261d159ffccdd4c1229c1343e387e060ab9162afaf2f60a172453","type":"image"},{"sequence":2,"text":"Input: s1 = \"aabcc\", s2 = \"dbbca\", s3 = \"aadbbcbcac\"\nOutput: true\nExplanation